The paper deals with deep neural networks applied to computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of residual networks and the development of new architectures for deep neural networks suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. However, the focus on computer vision tasks and the use of convolutional neural networks suggest that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The use of theoretical frameworks and mathematical interpretations suggest that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of natural language processing tasks suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
